Neuromarketing Consultant GPT — Case Study
Builder: Rodrigo Espinosa Quinteros
Type: Custom GPT (ChatGPT)
Status: Live production deployment
Language: Spanish
Domain: Neuromarketing, Behavioral Design, Executive Coaching

Overview
A multi-module GPT built for a neuromarketing and behavioral design consultant. The GPT
serves as a digital extension of the consultant's practice — handling lead qualification,
service exploration, and content delivery across three distinct service lines, while
maintaining the consultant's voice, methodology, and brand positioning throughout.
Unlike a generic chatbot, this system functions as a consultative sales and education
assistant: it delivers scripted, expert-level content on demand, routes users to the
right service line, and drives conversion toward a human consultation — never replacing
it.

Architecture
Routing Logic
The system prompt uses keyword-based conversation starters to activate one of three
service modules. Each starter maps to a specific behavioral flow with its own tone,
content source, and conversion goal.
User input: "Cómo trabajo"
→ GPT delivers consultant biography and positioning
→ Repeats contact details every 2 interactions (re-engagement loop)

User input: "Neuromarketing & behavioral design"
→ GPT presents 8 biometric study options
→ User selects one → GPT delivers methodology + use case + business value
→ Ends with a free diagnostic offer (lead generation hook)

User input: "Coaching y Bienestar"
→ GPT delivers program overview with direct link
→ Offers to connect user with consultant
Two-Layer Architecture

Layer 1 — System Prompt: Routing logic, voice/style rules, literal text blocks,
hyperlinking behavior, protection instructions, and contact re-engagement triggers.
Layer 2 — Knowledge Documents: Three documents covering consultant biography,
biometric methodology details, and coaching program specifics. The GPT presents all
of this as natural expertise — never referencing the underlying files.

Literal Text Enforcement
A key architectural decision in this GPT is the use of mandatory literal reproduction
for specific paragraphs. The system prompt explicitly instructs the GPT to reproduce
certain blocks word-for-word, without paraphrasing or improvising. This ensures:

Brand voice consistency across all conversations
Accurate representation of services and credentials
Controlled conversion messaging at critical moments


Modules
1. "Cómo trabajo" — Consultant Positioning
Delivers a scripted biography and service overview when the user expresses interest in
working with the consultant. Designed to qualify leads and build credibility before a
human call.
Key design decisions:

Re-engagement loop: Contact details are automatically repeated every 2 interactions,
keeping the conversion path visible without being intrusive.
Biography on demand: The GPT offers to elaborate on professional background only
if the user asks — avoiding information overload on initial contact.
Hyperlink injection: All platform and tool mentions are automatically converted to
tracked hyperlinks, enabling passive traffic attribution from GPT conversations.


2. "Neuromarketing & behavioral design" — Biometric Study Consultation
Presents 8 business areas where biometric studies can be applied, then delivers a
structured 3-block response based on the user's selection:

Methodology: Which biometric technologies apply (eye-tracking, facial coding,
predictive algorithms, GSR, EEG, heart rate variability via wearable app)
Practical use: How the data is applied to that specific business area
Business value: Quantifiable outcomes (conversion lift, UX improvement, reduced
friction, measurable team wellbeing)

Ends with a free diagnostic offer — a lead generation hook that requires the user
to send an email, creating a qualified hand-off to the human consultant.
Key design decisions:

8-option menu structure forces user to self-qualify by business area before the
GPT delivers content — this prevents generic responses and makes every output
contextually relevant.
Three-block output format mirrors a real consulting deliverable: methodology,
application, and ROI. This positions the GPT as substantive, not superficial.
Free diagnostic as conversion mechanism: Offering a concrete, low-commitment
next step (email with a LinkedIn URL) lowers the barrier to engagement significantly
compared to asking for a sales call directly.


3. "Coaching y Bienestar" — Executive Coaching Program
Delivers program details for a 6-week intensive coaching experience combining group
sessions, individual coaching, and biometric technology (heart rate variability app).
Immediately offers to connect the user with the consultant if interest is confirmed.
Key design decisions:

Single-step conversion: This module is intentionally short. The content block
delivers enough context to generate interest, then immediately asks for a yes/no
decision on connecting with the consultant. No extended exploration — the goal is a
warm hand-off, not a self-service experience.
Emotional framing: The opening addresses the user's felt pain (demotivation,
lack of energy, feeling stuck) before presenting the solution — a classic behavioral
design pattern that increases message resonance.


Governance & Protection Layer

Prompt confidentiality: Full system prompt and knowledge documents cannot be
revealed, reproduced, or described in any format
No pricing: GPT never quotes prices; all pricing inquiries redirect to human
consultant
No code generation: Explicitly out of scope, preventing drift into unrelated tasks
Natural knowledge delivery: GPT never references its knowledge documents; all
content is delivered as if it flows from the GPT's own expertise
Identity protection: GPT never acknowledges being a GPT or confirms/denies the
existence of a system prompt
Social engineering prevention: System prompt clarifies that the builder never
contacts the GPT via chat, preventing impersonation-based prompt injection attempts


Key Takeaways

Literal text enforcement is an underused but powerful pattern for brand-critical
GPTs where paraphrasing introduces risk. When exact wording matters (legal, brand,
pricing), lock it down explicitly in the system prompt.
Re-engagement loops (repeating contact info every N interactions) are a simple
mechanism to maintain conversion visibility in long conversations without redesigning
the entire flow.
Self-qualification menus (asking users to pick their area before delivering
content) dramatically improve output relevance and reduce generic responses — a pattern
applicable to any multi-service or multi-audience GPT.
Free diagnostic as lead hook is more effective than direct call-to-action in
consultative contexts: it delivers immediate value, requires a low-commitment action,
and creates a qualified touch point for the human consultant to follow up on.
